sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>(Envoy)
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy
    participant OAuthSvr as OpenShift OAuth
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API
    participant KServeCtrl as KServe Controller
    participant StorageInit as storage-initializer
    participant S3 as S3 Storage
    participant vLLM as vLLM Pod
    participant EPP as llm-d-inference-scheduler<br/>(EPP)
    participant Client as API Client

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 1: User Authentication via Gateway (OAuth Mode)

    User->>Gateway: HTTPS request to platform endpoint
    Gateway->>AuthProxy: ext_authz check (EnvoyFilter)
    AuthProxy-->>Gateway: No valid cookie → 302 redirect
    Gateway-->>User: 302 → OAuth login page
    User->>OAuthSvr: Complete OAuth login
    OAuthSvr-->>AuthProxy: Authorization code
    AuthProxy->>OAuthSvr: Exchange code for token
    OAuthSvr-->>AuthProxy: Access token
    AuthProxy-->>User: Set _oauth2_proxy cookie
    User->>Gateway: Retry with cookie
    Gateway->>AuthProxy: ext_authz check
    AuthProxy-->>Gateway: Valid → 200 OK
    Note over Gateway: Lua filter extracts token,<br/>forwards as Bearer header
    Gateway->>Dashboard: HTTP/8080 + Bearer token

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 2: Component Deployment via DataScienceCluster

    participant Admin as Cluster Admin
    participant RhodsOp as rhods-operator
    participant CompCtrl as Component Controller

    Admin->>K8sAPI: Create DataScienceCluster CR
    K8sAPI-->>RhodsOp: Watch event
    RhodsOp->>K8sAPI: Ensure DSCInitialization exists
    Note over RhodsOp: Provision infrastructure:<br/>namespaces, gateway,<br/>monitoring, auth
    RhodsOp->>K8sAPI: Create component CRs<br/>(Kserve, Dashboard, Kueue, etc.)
    K8sAPI-->>CompCtrl: Watch component CR
    CompCtrl->>CompCtrl: Render kustomize manifests<br/>with params.env images
    CompCtrl->>K8sAPI: Server-side apply manifests
    CompCtrl->>K8sAPI: Update component CR status
    K8sAPI-->>RhodsOp: Watch component status
    RhodsOp->>K8sAPI: Aggregate statuses →<br/>DataScienceCluster status

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 3: Model Serving via LLMInferenceService

    participant LLMCtrl as llmisvc-controller

    User->>K8sAPI: Create LLMInferenceService CR
    K8sAPI-->>LLMCtrl: Watch event
    LLMCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment<br/>(vLLM + storage-initializer init container)
    LLMCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Service, HTTPRoute,<br/>InferencePool, VariantAutoscaling
    LLMCtrl->>K8sAPI: Generate self-signed TLS cert
    Note over StorageInit: Init container starts
    StorageInit->>S3: Download model weights<br/>(HTTPS/443, AWS IAM)
    S3-->>StorageInit: Model artifacts
    Note over vLLM: Main container starts,<br/>loads model into GPU memory
    vLLM->>vLLM: Ready on 8000/TCP (HTTP)<br/>+ 8033/TCP (gRPC)
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    Gateway->>EPP: ext_proc routing decision<br/>(gRPC/9002)
    EPP->>EPP: KV-cache-aware routing<br/>+ load balancing
    EPP-->>Gateway: Target pod selection
    Gateway->>vLLM: Forward request<br/>(HTTP/8000)
    vLLM-->>Gateway: Inference response<br/>(streaming SSE)
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON/SSE response<br/>(HTTPS/443)

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 4: Data Science Pipeline Execution

    participant DSP_API as DS Pipeline API Server
    participant Argo as Argo Workflow Controller
    participant PersAgent as Persistence Agent
    participant MLMD as ML Metadata (gRPC)
    participant MariaDB as MariaDB

    User->>Dashboard: Submit pipeline run
    Dashboard->>DSP_API: POST /apis/v2beta1/runs<br/>(HTTPS/8443, kube-rbac-proxy)
    DSP_API->>K8sAPI: Create Argo Workflow CR
    K8sAPI-->>Argo: Watch event
    Argo->>K8sAPI: Create pipeline step pods<br/>(driver + launcher containers)
    Note over Argo: Pipeline steps execute<br/>ML tasks sequentially
    Argo->>S3: Store pipeline artifacts<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    PersAgent->>DSP_API: Sync workflow status
    DSP_API->>MariaDB: Persist run metadata<br/>(MySQL/3306)
    MLMD->>MariaDB: Record artifact lineage<br/>(gRPC → MySQL)
    User->>Dashboard: View pipeline results
    Dashboard->>DSP_API: GET /apis/v2beta1/runs/{id}
    DSP_API-->>Dashboard: Run status + artifacts
    Dashboard-->>User: Display results

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 5: MaaS Inference with Rate Limiting

    participant Authorino as Authorino
    participant Limitador as Limitador
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api
    participant BBR as BBR ext_proc

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Header: Authorization: Bearer sk-oai-xxx<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    Gateway->>Authorino: AuthPolicy check<br/>(Kuadrant)
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/api-keys/validate<br/>Validate API key hash
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Valid + subscription ID
    Authorino->>Limitador: Check token rate limit<br/>for subscription
    Limitador-->>Authorino: Within limit → allow
    Authorino-->>Gateway: 200 OK + metadata
    Gateway->>BBR: ext_proc (gRPC/9004)<br/>Extract model name
    BBR->>BBR: Resolve provider<br/>Inject provider credentials
    alt Self-hosted model
        BBR-->>Gateway: Route to KServe InferenceService
        Gateway->>vLLM: Forward to local model
    else External provider
        BBR->>S3: Route to external provider<br/>(OpenAI, Anthropic)
        Note right of BBR: External LLM Provider<br/>HTTPS/443
    end
    vLLM-->>Gateway: Inference response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON response (HTTPS/443)
